    "narrative": "For the Zurich Zebras, today\u2019s slate is headlined by the elite potential of **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (82.13), who occupies the optimal spot for a breakout performance against a struggling arm. His high score is fueled by a massive +19% SP skill advantage and favorable wind conditions, making him our priority start for stolen base production. Following him, **Junior Caminero** (65.79) and **Trea Turner** (65.20) anchor the offense; **Trea Turner** specifically benefits from an ideal leadoff spot and a moderate xERA matchup against Junk, ensuring his high-floor speed contributions remain at the forefront of our strategy. **Carson Benge** (63.27) also grades out strongly due to a significant park factor boost, though he remains a high-variance play given the lingering 39% rain risk that threatens a potential mid-game delay.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision was balancing the bench depth against our efficiency targets. **Dillon Dingler** (56.65) narrowly edged out internal utility options to secure the C1 spot, primarily due to his favorable dynamic platoon advantage against Tolle. While **Luke Raley** (56.15) holds a respectable score, he sits right on the edge of our \"marginal\" threshold; he only narrowly cleared the cut because of his significant platoon edge against a hittable right-hander. Conversely, our bench remains largely depleted of active talent, with **Christian Yelich** and **Lars Nootbaar** both sidelined on the IL, while **Caleb Durbin** and **Zac Veen** lack the active status required to challenge for a spot. The lineup is now set, with the focus shifting to **Yordan Alvarez** (63.86) to provide the necessary power surge against Yamamoto, despite the tougher SP xERA grade.",
